The paper deals with secrecy in communication networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS subfields. The use of common randomness and conferencing links suggests that the paper is related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The mention of practical networks also suggests that the paper may be relevant to multimedia systems (cs.MM), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and security and privacy (cs.SI).
